      "role": "user",
      "content": "It feels so very heavy... like this heavy silk gown is pulling me down into the earth itself. If I were to truly find that peace you speak of, would it be a violent storm, or would it be as quiet as the falling snow? I want it to be quiet. I want to slip away so softly that even the shadows wouldn't notice I was gone. How does one truly find that final, silent rest?",
